The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 22: The RBI has allowed banks to issue guarantees beyond 10 years to customers to keep pace with the long-term loans extended by them. However, while issuing such guarantees, the banks should take into account the impact of issues with very long duration on their asset liability management.                             
	 New Delhi, April 22: Audit firm Price Waterhouse (PW) has appointed former cabinet secretary Naresh Chandra and former Comptroller and Auditor General of India V.K. Shunglu as advisers as part of its efforts to boost its reputation.                             
	 Mumbai, April 22: Jet Airways has lost 13 pilots to Doha-based Qatar Airways. Thirteen pilots have put in their papers to join Qatar Airways and many more resignations are in the pipeline, a Jet Airways source said.                            
	 New Delhi, April 22: The committee of secretaries, which met today, is believed to have decided against the ban on futures trading in sugar as of now. It has asked the commodity market regulator FMC to monitor prices and check excessive speculation.                            
	 New Delhi, April 22: Reliance Industries has signed agreements to sell natural gas from its KG-D6 fields to at least six power producers in Andhra Pradesh, including GVK Power.                                                                                                                           
